Source: libapache2-modsecurity3
Section: httpd
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ervin Hegedus <airween@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 11), apache2-dev, libmodsecurity-dev (>=3.0.3)
Standards-Version: 4.1.3
Homepage: https://github.com/SpiderLabs/ModSecurity-apache
#Vcs-Browser: https://salsa.debian.org/debian/libapache2-modsecurity3
#Vcs-Git: https://salsa.debian.org/debian/libapache2-modsecurity3.git

Package: libapache2-modsecurity3
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: The ModSecurity-apache connector is the connection point
 between Apache and libmodsecurity (ModSecurity v3). Said another way,
 this project provides a communication channel between Apache and
 libmodsecurity. This connector is required to use LibModSecurity
 with Apache.
 The ModSecurity-apache connector takes the form of an Apache module.
 The module simply serves as a layer of communication between Apache
 and ModSecurity.

